The Nigeria Police, Osun State Command, on Wednesday paraded six suspected serial armed robbery suspects that have been terrorizing some communities in the state.
The Police disclosed that dangerous weapons such as double barrel guns, cutlasses and some charms were recovered from the suspects.
The Commissioner of Police in Osun State, Abiodun Ige, said the suspects have made useful statements and confessed to their various robbery operations, adding that at the conclusion of the investigation,Â  they will be charged to court.
The CP appealed for cooperation of the media and the public by giving necessary information that will help the police in nipping criminal activities in the bud.

			
